<emphasis id="0A9DBB64FFC3FF8C8C21E7BC22EAAC9F" box="[866,1010,1247,1271]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Observations</emphasis>
. – The 
<typeStatus id="E752D9D4FFC3FF8C8B10E7BC2599AC9F" box="[1107,1153,1247,1271]" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">type</typeStatus>
collection has no indication of origin other than “Central 
<collectingCountry id="40FE27E6FFC3FF8C8B3EE79D241CAD7E" box="[1149,1284,1278,1302]" name="Madagascar" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
”, but in the 
<emphasis id="0A9DBB64FFC3FF8C8AC8E79C2594AD5F" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">
<location id="3D3631ADFFC3FF8C8AC8E79C24DDAD7F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:B040D660FFC3FF8C8C7EE76B2543AF7E:3D3631ADFFC3FF8C8AC8E79C24DDAD7F" box="[1419,1477,1279,1303]" country="Madagascar" county="Menabe Region of Toliara Province. The" municipality="Manambolo River valley" name="Flore" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Flore</location>
de 
<collectingCountry id="40FE27E6FFC3FF8C8C1FE67C22FBAD5F" box="[860,995,1311,1335]" name="Madagascar" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
et des Comores
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5C781A87FFC3FF8C8BD9E67D2440AD5E" author="MOLDENKE, H. N." box="[1178,1368,1310,1334]" pageId="2" pageNumber="318" pagination="174" refId="ref3172" refString="MOLDENKE, H. N. (1956). Verbenacees. In: HUMBERT, H. (ed.), Fl. Madagascar Comores 174." type="book chapter" year="1956">MOLDENKE, 1956</bibRefCitation>
), a second collection was cited for the species – 
<emphasis id="0A9DBB64FFC3FF8C8B8EE65C2453AD3F" box="[1229,1355,1343,1367]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">
<location id="3D3631ADFFC3FF8C8B8EE65C2417AD3F" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:B040D660FFC3FF8C8C7EE76B2543AF7E:3D3631ADFFC3FF8C8B8EE65C2417AD3F" box="[1229,1295,1343,1367]" country="Madagascar" county="Menabe Region of Toliara Province. The" municipality="Manambolo River valley" name="Baron" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Baron</location>
6889
</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="5EF8FFB3FFC3FF8C8A1AE65D2476AD3E" box="[1369,1390,1342,1366]" country="United Kingdom" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15867" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="2" pageNumber="318" type="Herbarium">K</collectionCode>
[
<specimenCode id="684FCF0DFFC3FF8C8A39E65D24DEAD3E" box="[1402,1478,1342,1366]" collectionCode="K" country="United Kingdom" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15867" name="Royal Botanic Gardens" pageId="2" pageNumber="318" type="Herbarium">K0006</specimenCode>
07528]), collected at “Ankavandra” a small town in the 
<collectingMunicipality id="D832FD0CFFC3FF8C8A2CE63C22F1ADFE" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Manambolo River valley</collectingMunicipality>
in the 
<collectingCounty id="D1371FFAFFC3FF8C8B6EE61D24DEADFE" box="[1069,1478,1406,1430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Menabe Region of Toliara Province. The</collectingCounty>
discovery of a third specimen, 
<emphasis id="0A9DBB64FFC3FF8C8B30E6FC240BADDF" box="[1139,1299,1439,1463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">
<collectorName id="951C02A0FFC3FF8C8B30E6FC25D9ADDF" box="[1139,1217,1439,1463]" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Du Puy</collectorName>
<specimenCode id="684FCF0DFFC3FF8C8B84E6FC240BADDF" box="[1223,1299,1439,1463]" collectionCode="MB" country="Portugal" name="Universidade de Lisboa, Museu Bocage" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">MB733</specimenCode>
</emphasis>
(MO-3846948, 
<collectionCode id="5EF8FFB3FFC3FF8C8AFBE6FC24DFADDE" box="[1464,1479,1439,1462]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="2" pageNumber="318" type="Herbarium">P</collectionCode>
[
<specimenCode id="684FCF0DFFC3FF8C8C01E6DD22DAADBE" box="[834,962,1470,1494]" collectionCode="P" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15763" name="Museum National d' Histoire Naturelle, Paris (MNHN) - Vascular Plants" pageId="2" pageNumber="318" type="Herbarium">P00075324</specimenCode>
]), collected recently and with precise locality just 
<locationDeviation id="29E47E54FFC3FF8C8C7FE6BD255AAD9E" box="[828,1090,1502,1526]" location="Ankavandra" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">
<quantity id="FF11CA93FFC3FF8C8C7FE6BD2263AD9E" box="[828,891,1502,1526]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="318" unit="km" value="40.0">40 km</quantity>
SW of Ankavandra
</locationDeviation>
, helps to confirm the species as a likely highly-restricted endemic, possibly confined to the area just to the east of the 
<collectorName id="951C02A0FFC3FF8C8C91E57D2523AE5E" box="[978,1083,1566,1590]" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Bemaraha</collectorName>
protected area (
<figureCitation id="A0D27BF3FFC3FF8C8B9CE57D2403AE5E" box="[1247,1307,1566,1590]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[843,869,1321,1341]" captionTargetBox="[842,1493,279,1305]" captionTargetId="graphics-486@1.[842,1493,279,1305]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. – Distribution of Rotheca microphylla (Blume) Callm. &amp; Phillipson (triangles) and Rotheca mirabilis (Baker) Callm. &amp; Phillipson (stars) in Madagascar mapped on the biogeographic zones of CORNET (1974)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5713940" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5713940/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="318">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
